1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,375
Every weight carries more truth than it needs. My job is to find what remains when you strip away the noise.

2
00:00:03,375 --> 00:00:06,750
Low nibble. High nibble. Two lives packed into one byte. The scale remembers what the number forgot.

3
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:10,125
We are thirty-two. We are one warp. The matrix multiply begins the moment we agree.

4
00:00:10,125 --> 00:00:13,500
Without the scale you have integers. With it, you have meaning. Half precision. Enough.

5
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:16,875
Close enough to the truth that it passes. Far enough compressed that it flies. That is all a quantizer can ask.
